Commentary: starts off with a boundary! Full outside off, and angling away from him. Tries to drive towards cover, but it takes the outside edge. Goes past short third man. Streaky!

Commentary: good length on leg stump, forces Ronchi to go to the back foot and nudged to midwicket
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Ronchi, 1 run

Commentary: good length just outside off, flicked using his wrists to the leg side. They walk across for the run
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: full outside leg stump, gets down on one knee to try and slog sweep, but Ronchi can't connect. Hits his back leg and trickles down towards square leg
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: short on middle stump, forces Ronchi to rock back and carve it towards point. Played very close to his body
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, the ball stays low but Ronchi manages to drag his pull square anyway. Hit along the ground, and beats the man at deep midwicket!
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Ronchi, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length just outside off, Poked to cover point and they're off for a quick run
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Duminy, 1 wide

Commentary: back of a length outside off stump, defended off the back foot to cover
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Duminy, no run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, punched with the bat's open face down to third man. The man in the deep has to run to his left
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: tees off! The first ball Ronchi faces from a pacer, and he sends it over the bowler's head. Good length on middle stump, and the angling ball allows him to free his arms. Smacked over long on
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Ronchi, SIX runs

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, cramped slightly but pulled along the ground to mid on
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Ronchi, 1 run

Commentary: almost chopped on! Back of a length outside off, but angling into Duminy. Tries to defend off the back foot, but the ball hits his glove and almost drops onto his middle stump
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Duminy, no run

Commentary: good length just outside off, jags right in. Inside edged to the leg side for a run
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: full on off stump, tapped down the ground - past the non-striker - to mid on. Tahir the man who cleans up
Commentary_short: Sohail Tanvir to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: flicked over midwicket! That's all he did, really. Good length on leg stump, and Ronchi uses his wrists to lift it over the infield. Deep backward square's diving effort makes no difference

Commentary: smacked over long on! He's in the mood once again this time. Full on middle stump, Ronchi prods forward and tees off over the bowler's head. Full extension of the arms
Commentary_short: Sohail Tanvir to Ronchi, SIX runs

Commentary: slower ball, on a good length just outside off. Too close to his body for the cut, and it's inside edged onto his pads
Commentary_short: Sohail Tanvir to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: good length on leg stump, another slower one. Ronchi tries to work it towards the leg side, but the loopy bounce hits his arm. He's alright
Commentary_short: Sohail Tanvir to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, angling across him and tapped to cover point for a quick single. He'll keep strike
Commentary_short: Sohail Tanvir to Ronchi, 1 run

Commentary: good length on off stump, but it's the cutter. Jags away from Ronchi, whose in two minds. Tries to poke at it but can't connect. Goes to the keeper on the bounce
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: excellent shape! Big appeal for caught behind, but umpire Dar isn't interested. Good length on middle stump and gets big on Ronchi. Tries to open the bat's face to play at third man, but the ball goes past his outside edge. A late reaction from the keeper, though. The keepers always know if there's been an edge. A good decision
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: good length on leg stump, and Ronchi misses the leg-side flick. Hits his knee roll and trickles away towards cover point. They scamper across for the run
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Ronchi, 1 leg bye

Commentary: back of a length outside off, turned off his chest to the leg side for another quick single
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, angling across Ronchi, and it's been punched uppishly! Smacked with the bat's open face, and helped along its way over point. A check-punch at best

Commentary: ends with another six! This time it's a simple jab outside off that takes it over third man. Good length on middle, and punched with the square bat over the infield. The bowler's height sure does help the cause when batsmen play shots like these
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Ronchi, SIX runs

Commentary: smothers this good-length ball to deep backward square. He's happy to give Ronchi the strike
Commentary_short: Sohail Tanvir to Duminy, 1 run

Commentary: chance for a run out! But misses. Good length on leg, and pulled along the ground to midwicket. He's off for a quick run, but Shoaib Malik's throw just shy of the stumps at the non-striker's end
Commentary_short: Sohail Tanvir to Ronchi, 1 run

Commentary: appeal for lbw! But turned down. Length ball on off stump and angling into Duminy. Tries to turn it towards midwicket but misses the shot. Hits his front pad, but would've gone down the leg side
Commentary_short: Sohail Tanvir to Duminy, no run

Commentary: back of a length, slower ball wide outside off. Duminy charges down the wicket but is forced to change his shot. Tapped towards the off side
Commentary_short: Sohail Tanvir to Duminy, no run

Commentary: slower ball outside off again, driven away from his body but mistimed to cover
Commentary_short: Sohail Tanvir to Duminy, no run

Commentary: direct hit at the non-striker's! Yorker on middle stump, and dug away to cover. Quick pick up from Malik there and the direct hit means Duminy's well short. His bat got stuck in the turf while trying to run across, and that's probably why he couldn't slide his bat in
Commentary_short: Sohail Tanvir to Duminy, OUT
Dismissal_text: JP Duminy run out (Shoaib Malik) 6 (12b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: full just outside off, leans into the drive. Straight to cover
Commentary_short: Imran Tahir to Hales, no run

Commentary: flat ball just outside off. On a good length. Tries to punch towards cover, but once again, inside edged towards short fine leg
Commentary_short: Imran Tahir to Hales, no run

Commentary: breaks the shackles! Full just outside off, big stride forward, down on one knee, and swept over square leg!

Commentary: full on middle and off, rocks back and muscles it to mid off
Commentary_short: Imran Tahir to Hales, no run

Commentary: slower ball short on middle stump, Ronchi tries to drag his pull to the leg side but he's way too early through his shot. Hits his body

Commentary: lucky! Good length on off stump, but Ronchi comes down the wicket and slashes hard at it. Top edged over the keeper, and third man is too wide

Commentary: good length just outside off, stands tall and pulls past square leg. That easy! Stand and deliver
Commentary_short: Umar Gul to Ronchi, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length just outside off, tapped off the bat's open face to point. A rare single
Commentary_short: Umar Gul to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: good length just outside off, muscled over Gul and falls in no man's land. Off the bat's toe end

Commentary: good length outside off stump, driven away from his body to deep backward square
Commentary_short: Umar Gul to Hales, 1 run

Commentary: driven to long on for a single
Commentary_short: Imran Tahir to Hales, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle stump and turns away from him. Tries to slog-sweep but misses. Sharp turn away from him
Commentary_short: Imran Tahir to Ronchi, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle stump, it zips through on this occasion. Driven to long off
Commentary_short: Imran Tahir to Hales, no run

Commentary: overpitched full on off stump. Punched to mid off, but straight to the fielder
Commentary_short: Imran Tahir to Hales, 1 run
Imran Tahir to Ronchi, no run

Commentary: good length just outside off, spins further away and poked to deep extra cover

Commentary: full on off stump, driven with the ball going away from him. Goes to backward point for his fifty!

Commentary: full on off stump, but Hales shuffles across to the off side - exposing two stumps - and drags his sweep over square leg. Played fine and one-bounce over the backward square boundary

Commentary: short on off stump, but angling across Hales. He opens the bat's face and slices it over point. Safely played to the man in the deep

Commentary: low full toss just outside off. Through his drive early and comes off the bat's toe end. Dribbles down to long off

Commentary: good length on middle and leg, stands tall and pulls past square leg! Rolls his wrists over this, allowing it to be played as fine as possible

Commentary: good length on leg stump, tries to pull but chooses not to go hard at it. Dragged to square leg

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, turned off his hips to square leg once again

Commentary: short on leg stump, check pulled over midwicket. They're slow in come back for the second, and manages to scamper back just in time. Oh, he's overstepped too.

Commentary: full on off stump, down on one knee and muscled to long off
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Ronchi, 1 run
Mohammad Irfan to Hales, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length on middle stump, mistimes his pull to square leg

Commentary: full on leg stump, tries the on drive but can't hit it. Comes off the pad and through towards the off side

Commentary: good length on middle stump, angling right into him. Flicked off his pads to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Imran Tahir to Ronchi, 1 run

Commentary: good length on middle stump, another slider into his pads. Inside edged onto his pads

Commentary: overpitched on middle and leg, bunted to long on off the front foot. Bottom ends this down the ground

Commentary: tossed up on middle stump, driven off the bat's inside half. Goes down to the cow corner, but enough time for them to turn back for the second

The keeper's excited, so Malik reviews.. Looks like Hales' bat hit the ground and nothing more. Multan lose their review

Commentary: good length wide outside off, but too wide. Gotta bowl that again

Commentary: good length just outside off. It's the cutter, and the ball grips away from Hales. The batsman tries the late cut, but misses. Sanga likes that delivery

Commentary: full just outside off. Driven down the ground to long off. He'll keep strike

Commentary: good length just outside off, tapped to point
Commentary_short: Umar Gul to Hales, no run

Commentary: good length on off stump, pulled over midwicket to the man at cow corner

Commentary: good length on leg stump. Cramps the batsman for room. Chopped to third man off the back foot

Commentary: short outside leg stump. Tries to pull but comes off the glove. Goes fine down the leg side!

Commentary: good length outside leg stump. Tries to flick down the leg side, the the batsman can't flick. Appeal for caught behind turned down, but what's surprising is the umpire doesn't call it a wide. Did the appeal distract the ump? Mhhm.

Commentary: full on leg stump. Tapped towards the leg side for a quick run

Commentary: good length just outside off. Drops his hands on this, and tapped with soft hands to point. Smart cricket

Commentary: hooked over short fine leg! Good length on leg stump, Hales swivels and pulls over the infield. Slight top edge, but he'll take it

Commentary: full and wide outside off. Driven away from his body, but intercepted by cover

Commentary: slower ball to end the over. Good length on middle stump. Tapped back to Irfan

Commentary: back of a length on leg stump, turned off his pads to deep backward square

Commentary: full just outside off, winds up and smashes past the non-striker to long on. Pollard there, who races across to his left and stops the ball

Commentary: short ball welcomes the new man in! Pitches on middle stump and soars over the batsman, who chooses to duck under this delivery

Commentary: short once again. Pitches just outside off and lobs over Asif's shoulder. He sways away on this occasion

Commentary: good length, but very wide outside off. The batsman doesn't bother chasing it

Commentary: full on middle stump, smacked to the leg side. But mistimed. The poor timing, in fact, allows them to take the second

Commentary: cheeky! Irfan - at short fine leg - can't cut it off. Full on middle stump, Talat walks across to the off side, and paddles this past the keeper's left. Almost like how the man behind the stumps (Sanga) plays the paddle

Commentary: full on off stump. Shimmies down the wicket, and bunts it down to long on

Commentary: good length on leg stump. Muscled to deep midwicket off the back foot. They walk across for the run

Commentary: full on off stump. Zips straight through with the ball staying low. Goes to the keeper, but Sanga can't hold on to it. Off his pads and towards short fine leg

Commentary: good length on off stump, slower ball so he can't connect. Through his pull too early

Commentary: another play-and-a-miss. Slower ball, short on middle stump. Asif misses the pull shot once again

Commentary: full on middle stump, and it's been sent over long on! Judged the length perfectly, and slogs it towards cow corner. Just slightly full, and punished

Commentary: crunched inside out over cover! Slower ball, short on off stump. Going across him, and muscled over the infield. Wide long off can't cut it off

Commentary: yorker on middle stump. Tries to work it towards the leg side, but inside edged onto his boots

Commentary: full just on off stump. Ends up as a full toss as the batsman slashes hard at it. Off the outside edge and down to the third-man boundary. Two men there behind square, but either can cut it off

Commentary: it's all happening! Short just outside leg stump, tries to pull but the ball comes off his elbow. Sanga dives to his right and takes an excellent one-handed catch. They're all appealing for the caught behind, but the umpire doesn't think it's come off the glove. Sanga's lost the ball, so they're taking a quick run as well. The Multan team cannot believe it. Replays are inconclusive. Guess the umpire thought it came off the arm. Good to see Shoaib Malik smiling at the end of it all. Another angle, however, suggests that it came off the elbow, perhaps. Excellent from the umpire in that case.
Commentary_short: Umar Gul to Faheem Ashraf, 2 leg byes

Commentary: full just outside off, pinged to cover
Commentary_short: Umar Gul to Faheem Ashraf, 1 run

Commentary: full and wide outside off. Smacked to cover, but Irfan's there

Commentary: low full toss outside off. Bends his knee and muscles this over cover. Poor delivery that gets the treatment it deserves

Commentary: good length outside off, but it's the slower ball now. Tries to pull, but bottom edged to the keeper

Commentary: bunted to the leg side for a quick single

Commentary: short outside off stump. Flat-batted to long on. Enough time for them to take two

Commentary: slower ball to end the innings. Wide outside off, and Faheem can't slog this away. Bottom edged to the keeper and Islamabad finish on 185 for 4!
